%N A396136 Number of digraphs on n labeled nodes such that every node is reachable from node 1 and node n is reachable from every node (node 1 = node n when n = 1).
%C A396136 Single-entry single-exit control-flow graphs on n labeled basic blocks (self-loops disallowed; multiply by 2^n to allow them), the virtual-entry/virtual-exit form used for simultaneous dominator and postdominator maintenance.
%C A396136 The acyclic analog with unspecified endpoints is A165950; here A165950(n) = n*(n-1)*(acyclic version of a(n)) for n >= 2.
%F A396136 a(n) = A396110(n) - Sum_{k=2..n-1} binomial(n-2,k-2) * a(k) * L_k(n-k) for n >= 2, a(1) = 1, where A396110(n) is the fixed-source initially connected count and L_m(n) = 2^(n*(n+m-1)) - Sum_{k=0..n-1} binomial(n,k) * 2^((n-k)*(n-1)) * L_m(k) is Robinson's lambda (every one of n vertices connected to a set of m externals).
%Y A396136 Cf. A165950, A345258, A350794, A396110.
%K A396136 nonn,new
%O A396136 1,2
%A A396136 _Gregory Morse_, Jul 13 2026
